# See https://help.github.com/articles/ignoring-files for more about ignoring files.
#
# If you find yourself ignoring temporary files generated by your text editor
# or operating system, you probably want to add a global ignore instead:
#   git config --global core.excludesfile '~/.gitignore_global'

#####=== Exclude ALL Hidden Files ===#####
# see: https://dev.to/gajus/gitignore-mistake-that-everyone-makes-44kb
.*

#####=== Ignore Procfiles used for Development ===#####
Procfile*

#####=== Include These Hidden Files ===#####
!*.template
!.eslintrc.js
!.flayignore
!.gitignore
!.gitkeep
!.keep
!.reek.yml
!.rspec
!.rubocop.yml
!.rubocop_todo.yml
!.ruby-version
!.ruumba.yml
!.ruumba_todo.yml

#####=== Ignore Files in Application ===#####
**/log/*
**/tmp/*

# Ignore master key for decrypting credentials and more.
#####=== Ignore Secrets ===#####
config/master.key

#####=== Ignore Compiled Assets/Packs directories ===#####
app/assets/builds/*
public/*/

#####=== Ignore Node/Yarn ===#####
**/node_modules
**/yarn-error.log
**/yarn-debug.log*
